ingredientsDesc: C-PTH Standards:One vial, labeled A, containing 0 ng/mL of C-PTH, and five vials, labeled B-F, containing concentrations of approximately 0.25, 1.0, 2.0, 5.0 and 10.0 ng/mL of C-PTH in a buffer with a protein stabilizer and sodium azide as a preservative.PTH [I-125] Reagent:One vial, containing < 5μCi (185 kBq) of [I-125]-labeled PTH in a buffer with a protein stabilizer and sodium azide as a preservative.PTH Antiserum:One vial, 11 mL, containing goat anti-PTH serum in a buffer with a protein stabilizer and sodium azide as a preservative.Precipitating Reagent:One bottle, 110 mL, containing donkey anti-goat gamma globulin serum in a buffer containing polyethylene glycol as a precipitating aid and sodium azide as a preservative.C-PTH Controls:Two vials, Levels I and II, 1 mL each, containing low and high concentrations of C-PTH in a buffer with a protein stabilizer and sodium azide as a preservative.
